Step 1: Identify the items that are considered liquid (quick assets). These include the following End amounts:
 • Cash on Hand: 3,537,257.19  
 • Bank Deposits: 4,579,000.00  
 • Interest Receivable: 14,869.76  
 • Accounts Receivable: 1,716,911.17

Step 2: Sum these items to determine total quick assets.  
 Quick Assets = 3,537,257.19 + 4,579,000.00 + 14,869.76 + 1,716,911.17  
  = 9,848,038.12

Step 3: Identify the Current Liabilities. From the balance sheet,  
 Total Current Liabilities = 967,271.87

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio using the formula:  
 Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Current Liabilities  
  = 9,848,038.12 / 967,271.87  
  ≈ 10.18

Thus, the quick ratio as of the end reporting period is approximately 10.18.

Now, the final answer in the required JSON format is:

{"solution": {"Quick Ratio": "10.18"}}
